 text embedded into the generated rule\n\n## userDefineFunc\n\n```javascript\nconst ts = require(\"typescript\");\n\nlet rule = {};\nmodule.exports.rule = rule;\n\nrule.userDefineFunc = function(rule, node, context) {\n    if (!rule.analysisVisitor || rule.analysisVisitor.visitorName !== \"TaintAnalysisVisitor\") {\n        return false;\n    }\n    if (!ts.isCallExpression(node)) {\n        return false;\n    }\n    return false;\n};\n```\n\nReturn semantics:\n\n| Return | Effect |\n|---|---|\n| `false` | Continue engine default analysis |\n| `true` | Skip default analysis for that node; use only when custom logic fully handles it |\n\n`userDefineFunc` has no try/catch wrapper in the engine. Catch expected errors inside the function and return `false`.\n\n## Useful Runtime APIs\n\n| API | Use |\n|---|---|\n| `rule.analysisVisitor.getCurrentTaintVarSet()` | Read/update current taint variables |\n| `rule.analysisVisitor.handleSinkTrace(...)` | Build a sink trace |\n| `rule.analysisVisitor.addBugReport(sinkName, vertex)` | Report a finding |\n| `context.getTaintContext()` | Current taint state |\n| `context.isTaintContext()` | Check if current context is tainted |\n| `MapOfVariable.getVarFromNode(node)` | Convert AST node to variable |\n| `util.findNodesByXpath(node, xpath)` | XPath AST lookup |\n| `ts.isCallExpression(node)` | TypeScript AST type guard |\n\nPrefer DSL field definitions for ordinary sources/sinks. Use JS extend-file for framework-specific AST traversal, custom source identification, result filtering, or bug-reporting logic that field matching cannot express.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
